What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Electric Motor Sales Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Electric Motor Sales Market

Growing focus on the technological advancements by the major manufacturers, rising demand for electric vehicles around the world, and increasing initiatives by the government to promote awareness in regards to the protection of environment are the major factors attributable to the growth of the electric motor sales market. Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the electric motor sales market will exhibit a CAGR of 6.20% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Therefore, the electric motor sales market value, which was USD 1,42,342.20 million would rocket up to USD 230,319.02 million by 2028.

Electric motors are based upon the principle or mechanism of electromagnetic induction. In other words, electric motors are the electro-mechanic devices that convert electrical energy into mechanical energy. Electric motors cost lower than the fossil fuel motors and are greatly durable, energy efficient, require low maintenance and have high endurance for fluctuating voltages.

Rising globalization and growth in the level of carbon emissions and air pollution will emerge as the major market growth driving factor. Growing penetration of green vehicles in the developing economies, surging focus on the technological advancements in the electric motors and advent of better insulation materials will further aggravate the market value. Growing expenditure to undertake research and development proficiencies and overall rise in the production of automobiles will further carve the way for the growth of the market.

However, dearth of knowledge and technological expertise and lack of awareness associated with the benefits of smart motors will act as a growth restraint for the market. Easy availability of low-quality and inexpensive electric motors will further dampen the growth rate of the market. Large scale technological limitations in the underdeveloped economies and fluctuations in the prices of raw materials will further challenge the market growth rate.

